-- RBS Will Shut Cash Equities Unit With 1,200 Staff, Times Reports
-- B y   S i m o n   P a c k a r d
-- 2012-01-07T12:26:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-07/rbs-will-shut-cash-equities-business-with-1-200-employees-times-reports.html
Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc (RBS)  will
close its cash equities unit, which employs about 1,200 people,
because of its small and irregular profits, the Times of London
reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the decision.  The business is one of the investment banking divisions
that won’t be retained in a longer-term plan to be announced
next week that aims to prepare the bank for the end of U.K.
state control, the newspaper said today.  While RBS hasn’t found a buyer for the entire equities
division, Oriel Securities Ltd, Numis Corp Plc. and  Jefferies
Group Inc. (JEF)  are interested in buying Hoare Govett, its small
corporate equities broking arm, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Packard in  London  at 
 packard@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
